This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a new method for reinforcement learning that extends Model Agnostic Meta Learning (MAML) for RL. It also uses observable dynamics of the environment instead of an explicit reward function in MAML's finetune step. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with the adaptation of agents to new environments and changes in dynamics. The paper may also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as efficient adaptation is critical for robots to operate in the real world. The paper may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category as it deals with the control of agents in dynamic environments. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it validates the method on common benchmark environments.
